name: AppConfig
desc: Stores important values or settings that need to be accessed at different parts of the app.

name: activeLessonIds
desc: List of those lesson ids, the user has selected and that are a part of the selected userClass.

name: configPath
desc: Get the path to the app_config.json file.

name: documentsDir
desc: Path to the application directory.

name: holidayStrings
desc: List of dates as strings that are holidays.

name: initConfig
desc: Call this method to init the class and to load the local config data.

name: isHoliday
desc: Checks if the date is a holiday based on holidayStrings property.

name: isSek2
desc: Checks if the user is in sek 2.

name: lessonIds
desc: List of all lesson ids the user has selected.

name: level
desc: Stores the level of the user.

name: loadConfigFileSync
desc: Load the current app_config.json file.

name: recreateDefaultConfig
desc: This method deletes the current config file and creates a new one with default values.

name: saveConfigFileSync
desc: Saves the current static variables to the app_config.json file.

name: sek2Threshold
desc: First level that is seen as sek 2.

name: setLessonIds
desc: Changes the lessonIds and saves the config file.

name: setLevel
desc: Changes the level and saves the config file.

name: setUserClass
desc: Changes the userClass and saves the config file.

name: storeGradesInCloud
desc: If grades should be uploaded to the cloud.

name: storeSettingsInCloud
desc: If settings and this app config should be uploaded to the cloud.

name: storeWizardInCloud
desc: If a level wizard settings should be stored in the cloud.

name: updateActiveLessonIds
desc:
Sets the active lesson ids as those ids, that are a.) present in lessonIds
and b.) are registered for the stored userClass as a valid lesson id.

name: userClass
desc: The class name of the user. Eg. 11A or 8D.

name: calculateExamWeight
desc: Override this function with a custom implementation that returns the appropriate exam weight for the given level and number of exams.

name: calendar
desc: Fetched data from the online calendar.

name: error
desc: Stores the latest error thrown by a fetch process.

name: getHipConfig
desc: Override this function with a custom implementation that returns the HipConfig for the current user.

name: hip
desc: Fetched data from the Home.InfoPoint service.

name: hipPath
desc: Path to the hip_wrapper.json file, where the data of this class is stored.

name: loadingState
desc: If the wrapper is currently handling any fetches.

name: mapPercentageToGrade
desc: Override this function with a custom implementation that returns the grade value for a given percentage and level.

name: onDataChanged
desc: A function that gets called every time new data has loaded in.

name: onLoadingStateChanged
desc: A function that gets called every time loadingState changes.

name: saveToCloud
desc: If the data should be saved to the cloud.

name: schedule
desc: Fetched data from the schedule of lessons.

name: timeoutDuration
desc:
Maximum time for fetching online data.
Defaults to 5 seconds.

name: userId
desc: Used to identify the user in the cloud.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: Grade.fromPoints
desc: Takes a string representation of the grade from 0 to 15.

name: Grade.fromStringValue
desc: Takes a string representation of the grade in decimal grade system. Can handle appendages (either "+" or "-").

name: appendage
desc: Either "+" or "-". If set to null, the grade value has no appendage.

name: date
desc: Implementation:

name: dateOfWriting
desc: Date on which e.g. the test was written.

name: decimalValue
desc: Use this setter to safely update the grade value if the input value is between 1 and 6 and might have an appendage like '+' or '-'.

name: description
desc: A description provided by the teacher on Home.InfoPoint.

name: ghost
desc: If the grade shall be excluded from calculations.

name: gradeValue
desc: Returns the value of the grade in the correct grade format.

name: hasData
desc: Opposite of isEmpty.

name: hasWeeklyExercises
desc: If this grade has weekly exercises stored.

name: isEmpty
desc: If AppConfig.isSek1 is set to true, checks if value is equal to null.

name: isExam
desc: Whether or not this grade is an exam.

name: key
desc:
If this grade was imported from Home.InfoPoint, set the key to the index of the row of the table from Home.InfoPoint,
that corresponds to this grade.

name: operator ==
desc: The equality operator.

name: points
desc: Value of the grade from 15 to 00.

name: pointsValue
desc: Use this setter to safely set the grade value if the input value is between 0 and 15. Can handle either a String or an integer representative.

name: seen
desc: Whether or not the user has seen this grade.

name: similarTo
desc: Compares this grade to other by their points value and isExam property.

name: stringValue
desc: Returns a string representation of the grade value depending on AppConfig.isSek2.

name: uploadDate
desc: Date on which the grade was uploaded to Home.InfoPoint.

name: userDescription
desc: A custom description set by the user.

name: value
desc: Value of the grade from 1 to 6.

name: weeklyExercises
desc: List of WeeklyExercise elements for storing the results of weekly exercises.

name: weeklyExercisesPercentage
desc: Returns the grade as a percentage of all weeklyExercises elements.

name: HipWrapper
desc: Contains all important data found on Home.InfoPoint.

name: HipWrapper.fromJson
desc: Reads the json file at the given path and constructs a HipWrapper instance.

name: addDataFromWrapper
desc: Takes another wrapper and adds additional data to this.

name: addGrade
desc: Add a Grade to the given Subject.

name: changedGrades
desc: List of SpecialGrade elements of those grades, that have changed since the last import.

name: currentSemesterIndex
desc: Returns the index of the last element of semesters where Semester.hasData is true.

name: fetchNewData
desc: Call this function to fetch new data from Home.InfoPoint.

name: canContinue
desc: If the loading state should allow the underlying process to continue.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: ScheduleWrapper
desc: Contains data for the school schedule.

name: changedLessons
desc: Returns a list of VPLesson elements that happen on the given date and have changes.

name: error
desc: Stores a reference to an error if the latest fetch process returns an error.

name: fetchVPData
desc: Fetches the newest schedule data.

name: getNextDate
desc: Returns the next school day.

name: hasError
desc: If the last fetch has raised an error.

name: vpDataToday
desc: Contains a reference to the schedule data of the next day. Use this to decrease loading time for widgets.

name: Semester
desc: A Semester stores a list of Subject elements and additional meta data for a semester.

name: addDataFromSemester
desc: Takes another Semester and adds additional data to this.

name: clear
desc: Delete all subjects. If keepStructure is set to true, only the grades are removed.

name: clone
desc: Creates a copy of this object.

name: cloneStructure
desc: Creates a copy of this object without the single grades.

name: hasData
desc: Returns true if at least one subject has at least one grade.

name: hasFinalGrades
desc: Returns true if at least one subject has a final grade.

name: isSek2
desc: Calls the provided decideIfSek2 method with Semester.level property of this.

name: label
desc: Label or name the semester is referred to. E.g. "11.2" or "8.1".

name: lastUpdate
desc: The date of the last update of this semester.

name: level
desc: Level of this semester.

name: locked
desc: If set to true, this semester should not be changed anymore by any means.

name: setAllGradesSeen
desc: Calls Subject.setAllGradesSeen on all elements of subjects.

name: setAllGradesSeenSync
desc: Calls Subject.setAllGradesSeenSync on all elements of subjects.

name: subjects
desc: List of Subject elements stored for this semester.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: SpecialGrade
desc: A SpecialGrade holds a reference to a Grade that has a special property.

name: SpecialGrade.new
desc: Creates an instance of SpecialGrade.

name: parentSemester
desc: The parent Semester of the parentSubject.

name: parentSubject
desc: The parent Subject of the grades.

name: primary
desc: Holds a reference to the "special" grade.

name: similarGrades
desc: List of all other grades, that might be similar to the primary grade.

name: Subject
desc: A Subject stores a list of Grade elements and additional meta data for a subject.

name: Subject.fromJson
desc: Creates a Subject instance from a json map.

name: Subject.new
desc: A Subject stores a list of Grade elements and additional meta data for a subject.

name: abbr
desc: Abbreviation for the subject. E.g. "ma" or "en".

name: addGradesFromSubject
desc: Takes another Subject and adds additional data to this.

name: allGrades
desc: List of all grade, online and custom.

name: clone
desc: Creates a duplicate of this.

name: cloneStructure
desc: Creates a duplicate of this without all grades.

name: customGrades
desc: All grades added by the user.

name: exams
desc: List of all exams, online and custom.

name: finalSemesterGrade
desc: The final grade of this subject for a semester.

name: getAvg
desc: Helper method used to calculate the average of a list of Grade elements.

name: getExamsAvg
desc: Returns the average of the exams. Does not round.

name: getExamsAvgRounded
desc: Returns the average of the exams. Does round the final result to two decimal places.

name: getTargetAvg
desc: Internal helper method used by gradesToImprove method.

name: getTestsAvg
desc: Returns the average of the tests. Does not round.

name: getTestsAvgRounded
desc: Returns the average of the tests. Does round the final result to two decimal places.

name: getTotalAvg
desc: Returns the total average of this subject.

name: getTotalAvgRounded
desc: Returns the total average of this subject. Does round the final result to two decimal places.

name: gradesToImprove
desc: Returns a list of tuples with a grade and a "Doability" percentage that the user would need to add to get in order to increase his subject average.

name: hasData
desc: Whether this subject has any grades stored.

name: hasUnseenGrades
desc: Whether this subject has any grades, where Grade.unSeen is true.

name: name
desc: Display name of the subject.

name: newOrSimilarGrades
desc: A list of all grades as SpecialGrade that either have Grade.unSeen set to true or have a possible duplicate.

name: onlineGrades
desc: All grades listed on Home.InfoPoint.

name: removeGrade
desc: Remove grade. Note that only grades from customGrades that where created by the user and be removed.

name: setAllGradesSeen
desc: Sets Grade.seen to true for all elements of onlineGrades and customGrades after a delay of 3 seconds.

name: setAllGradesSeenSync
desc: Sets Grade.seen to true for all elements of onlineGrades and customGrades.

name: similarGrades
desc: A list of all grades as SpecialGrade that where added by the user and might have one or more duplicate grades online.

name: tests
desc: List of all tests, online and custom.

name: toJson
desc: Converts this object into a json map.

name: unseenGrades
desc: A list of all grades as SpecialGrade where Grade.unSeen is true.

name: fetchServicesStatus
desc: get services status
